<body>
    <header>
        <h1>BallotFlow: Blockchain-based Voting System</h1>
    </header>
    <section>
        <h2>Problem Statement</h2>
        <div class="card">
            <p>Traditional voting systems are centralized and vulnerable to hacking, fraud, and inefficiencies. BallotFlow addresses these issues by leveraging blockchain for transparency and security.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Our Approach</h2>
        <div class="card">
            <p>Using Layer 2 scaling solutions like sidechains or rollups, we ensure secure, efficient handling of large-scale elections without compromising speed or efficiency.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <div class="card">
            <ul>
                <li>Immutable voting records to prevent tampering</li>
                <li>Automated vote counting for timely and accurate results</li>
                <li>Voter authentication using unique NFTs/tokens</li>
                <li>Decentralized system to eliminate single points of failure</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <h2>Technological Components</h2>
        <div class="card">
            <ul>
                <li>Ethereum blockchain for smart contracts and secure transactions</li>
                <li>Validators to verify votes and ensure compliance</li>
                <li>Government nodes for auditing results</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <h2>Planning Process</h2>
        <div class="card">
            <ol>
                <li>Weeks 1-2: Research & Initial Planning</li>
                <li>Weeks 3-4: Technical Architecture & Design</li>
                <li>Weeks 5-6: Prototyping</li>
                <li>Weeks 7-8: Testing & Refinement</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>
    <footer>
        <p>Developed by Ben Olivieri, Christopher Biniaris, Hakim Morris, and Jarett Chapman</p>
    </footer>
